>JD: EEGLOSV O11 VEG.S +30 465
#note need to block the triple-triple. I played VEGES instead of VOES so that, if she bingoes with a huge 100+ point bingo on row 15 (maybe a Q bingo) Mina would only have 1 tile to go out with, which should score less than if she makes a 2-tile outplay. This was I also know her rack if she tries to fish a tile, but I'm probably always blocking on row 15 anyway. The think I have to be careful about is drawing the Q, but since there are two spots (M13 and C12) I don't have to minimize turnover.
