>JD: AEILLOR 15D ROLLIE +24 489
#note this is a pretty fascinating position for me. The Q is in the bag and I know her rack. By playing ROLLIE at 15D, I threaten QUA out at C12, and also a Q spot at M13. However, I seriously considered an intentional phony bingo here, because if she then makes a play like WIFED at 15E or L8, I can Q-stick her! With correct play on her end, ROLLIE leads to a 98-point win for me, whereas phonying and then her playing WIFED and getting Q-stuck is a 129-point win. But when Mina sees that the Q is in the bag after my phony, she can make a significantly better pre-endgame play - WEND at 11D for 8, threatening FIQUE in two spots and cutting the spread to 86!, Another thing to think about is that if I phony bingo, I should create another Q spot so that she can't accept the bingo and then Q-stick me!! I was thinking about (R)O(Y)ALLIER* which creates a second Q spot. Last interesting tidbit is that if I just accept UNWIFED* and proceed with the Q-stick, I win by 98 with perfect play - same as my spread after ROLLIE with perfect play on her part!
